<h2 style="padding-top: 20px; color: #6296c8;">Description:</h2>
<p>DCG Display Plugin Data is a <a href="http://wordpress.org/plugins/" target="_blank">WordPress plugin</a>, helps you to display WordPress.org plugin data such as version, requires and compatible up to, release and last update date, number of downloads, rating, description, installation steps, faq and screenshots etc. into pages / posts using simple shortcode.</p>
<p><em>This is a very useful plugin for any Plugin Developer to display it&#8217;s plugin data (from WordPress.org) on website.</em></p>
<h2 style="padding-top: 20px; color: #6296c8;">Installation:</h2>
<ul style="list-style-type: none;">
<li>1. Upload the ‘<a href="http://wordpress.org/plugins/dcg-display-plugin-data/" target="_blank">dcg-display-plugin-data</a>’ folder to the ‘/wp-content/plugins/‘ directory</li>
<li>2. Activate the plugin through the ‘Plugins’ menu in WordPress.</li>
<li>3. That’s it!</li>
</ul>
<h2 style="padding-top: 20px; color: #6296c8;">FAQ:</h2>
<p><strong>What does this plugin do?</strong><br />
This plugin display WordPress.org plugin data such as version, requires and compatible up to, release and last update date, number of downloads, rating, description, installation steps, faq and screenshots etc. into pages / posts using simple shortcode.</p>
<p><strong>Any shortcode examples?</strong><br />
Shortcode examples are <a href="http://wordpress.org/plugins/dcg-display-plugin-data/" target="_blank">given here</a>.</p>
<p><strong>Will DCG Display Plugin Data slow my site down?</strong><br />
No.</p>
<p><strong>Any specific requirements for this plugin to work?</strong><br />
No.</p>
<p><strong>Is that it?</strong><br />
Pretty much, yeah</p>
